
ğŸ“ How to Create and Run a Bash Script in Vim
Open Vim and create a new file

vim FileName.sh
Press Enter
This opens the file in the Vim editor.

Press i to enter Insert Mode
You can now start typing your Bash script.

Type your script

#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello world"
Press Esc
This exits Insert Mode and returns you to Normal Mode.

Save and Exit Vim

:wq
Run the script

sh FileName.sh
Output:




nginx
Hello world
